chunks.html_content: You must register your business with your local Trading Standards office if you make, sell or use animal feed.
chunks.plain_content:
Register an animal feed business
You must register your business with your local Trading Standards office if you make, sell or use animal feed.

chunks.html_content: The process is different if you’re in Northern Ireland
chunks.plain_content:
Register an animal feed business
The process is different if you’re in Northern Ireland

chunks.html_content:
Follow these steps to register your animal feed business:

  1. Read about registering and applying for approval on the Food Standards Agency website

  2. Register your business with your local Trading Standards office. Find your nearest office using the postcode finder in the Trading Standards website

Contact your local Trading Standards office if you are not sure if you should be registered.

Contact the Food Standards Agency for more information.
